parameters: Sister Eleo: That's why I can't prepare any ransom!
Sister Eleo: You do know that we're poor, right!?
Roparo Plunder Squad Leader: 'Hey, did you know?'

Roparo Plunder Squad Member: Brother, I've told you many
times.

Roparo Plunder Squad Leader: I'm not good at calculations,
so explain it to me next time so I can understand.
Roparo Plunder Squad Member: Hey, sorry about that.

Roparo Plunder Squad Underling (I want to quit this place
soon)

Sister Eleo: Please, set us free! We should still be able to
atone for our sins.

Roparo Plunder Squad Leader: If we can't get a ransom, then
we have no choice but to make this girl earn it.

Roparo Plunder Squad Leader: Alright, let's contact the
slave trader for that fat guy!
Sister Eleo: Please stop! Release us for your own sake too!
Roparo Plunder Squad Leader: Shut up... Put a muzzle on her.

Sister Eleo: No... stop... help me, someone, help me!
Sophia-san, help me!!

Priestess Sophia: Ouch, a stone hit me right on the back of
my head~ Hehe, it looks painful, doesn't it?
Sister Eleo: Sophia-san, why are you here...
Priestess Sophia: Hehe, I came to rescue you, Eleo-chan.

Roparo Plunder Squad Leader: So there are a total of... five
girls.

Roparo Plunder Squad Member: If we do this well, our boss
will promote us. Let's sell these girls to the master of
Psema.

Roparo Plunder Squad Leader: It's better if we don't kill
them if possible, but... it's okay if there are a few
less... more is better.
Priestess Sophia: Now then, will everyone lend me a hand?

Clea: Of course, there are also personal reasons why I want
to ask.

Roparo Plunder Squad Leader: You're quite strong, aren't
you?
Roparo Plunder Squad Member: Alright, I'll train harder.

Roparo Plunder Squad Leader: Hey, little priestess, you were
saying something about wanting to save us, right?

Sister Eleo: Yes, it's still the same! Please, don't commit
any more sins!

Roparo Plunder Squad Leader: I hate all of you because you
never call for help when you need it the most.

Roparo Plunder Squad Leader: But that's just how life is.
You should witness the harsh reality there.
Sister Eleo: Stop! Don't get close to Sophia-san!
Would you like to skip the adult scene?

Do you want to start the battle over? If you choose No, it
will result in a game over.
Priestess Sophia: Eleo-chan, are you injured?

Sister Eleo: Yes... and please stop using '-chan' when
addressing me! I am senior to Sophia-san in the church, you
know!
Priestess Sophia: Hehe, that's right, isn't it?
Priestess Sophia: Well then, let's go back.
Sister Eleo: Yes... let's go back.
Clea: You mentioned 'Psema' earlier, didn't you?

Roparo Raiders Squad Leader: So, you were acquainted with
that person? Was your life not a good one?
Clea: Do you know where they are?

Roparo Raiders Squad Leader: He's a cautious man. He
wouldn't do something like meeting us directly.

Clea: Alright, I understand. We will have the guards escort
you.

Roparo Raiders Squad Leader: It doesn't matter... There's no
place left for us to live in this empire.
Clea: It seems like this is the place.
Thief Nora: Leave the physical work to me!
Mage Relm: Is it really okay to rely on a thief...?

Priestess Sophia: There's quite a substantial amount here.
It seems like they were quite hardworking.

Clea: I want to deliver it to Eleo-san, but will she receive
it properly?

Priestess Sophia: I don't think that's a problem. It's
common for sinners to donate in order to atone for their
sins.

Mage Relm: I'm sure this is also something that was stolen,
but it's impossible to return each item individually at this
point.
Thief Nora: It's quite heavy, so I'll carry it!
Mage Relm: Why is Nora-san a thief, I wonder?
Thief Nora: The person who helped us was a thief... Ahaha.
Thief Nora: I don't think I'm suited for this, yes.
